<!--template match = subSubSection[ancestor::treatment]--><tp:treatment-sec sec-type="diagnosis">
<!--template match = paragraph--><p>
Diagnosis
</p>
<!--template match = paragraph--><p>
This species is easily recognizable by its size, smaller to 
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>C. wollastoni</tp:taxon-name>
<!--template match = taxonomicNameLabel-->sp. nov.
and 
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>C. verticalis</tp:taxon-name>
, and brown colouration. It differs from the other 
Madeira
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>Cixius</tp:taxon-name>
in the following characters: (1) the basal half of the vellum is hump-shaped but is much narrower on the outer margin than in 
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>C. verticalis</tp:taxon-name>
; the apex is blunt, not scythe-shaped as in 
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>C. wollastoni</tp:taxon-name>
<!--template match = taxonomicNameLabel-->sp. nov.
and 
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>C. verticalis</tp:taxon-name>
; (2) the medioventral expansion of the theca is digitiform and more conspicuous and longer.
</p>
</tp:treatment-sec>
